            <feedback>Incorrect. It appears you have the wrong sign for the slope. The regression line equation has the form Y = intercept + (slope * X).</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="10">
            <feedback>Correct. The regression line equation has the form Y = intercept + (slope * X). In this example, Y = 5096 + (−491 * X), so the slope equals −491.</feedback>
